                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>Table, found fragmented (the top broken into multiple fragments), but fully restored: legs (travertine) are solid slabs towards the rear, but the front profile carved to lion claw feet, with feathers to the top, and a volute profile.; table top (marble) has a raised moulding aroudn the edge, recessed upper surface, and a cornice profile to the sides. Legs are 65.5 cm tall, 11.3 cm wide, dimensions below are those of the table top slab itself.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.marble" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">marble</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.table" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/157.html">table</objectType>
                                    <dimensions><!--table top-->
                                        <height unit="cm">7.8</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">145.7</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">72</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.complete"/>
		    </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>The text is inscised in a single line along the right half of the smooth lower portion of the front profile, with a two-step moulding projecting above. Text is 494 mm long.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
